liurenjie1024 commented on issue #4450: ARROW-5463: [Rust] Add AsRef trait for Buffer.
URL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/4450#issuecomment-498499428


   @sunchao It helps with bool type. But if we need to add support for u8, we need to remove this piece of code:
   ```rust
   /// Creating a `Buffer` instance by copying the memory from a `AsRef<[u8]>` into a newly
   /// allocated memory region.
   impl<T: AsRef<[u8]>> From<T> for Buffer {
       fn from(p: T) -> Self {
           // allocate aligned memory buffer
           let slice = p.as_ref();
           let len = slice.len() * mem::size_of::<u8>();
           let capacity = bit_util::round_upto_multiple_of_64(len);
           let buffer = memory::allocate_aligned(capacity);
           unsafe {
               memory::memcpy(buffer, slice.as_ptr(), len);
           }
           Buffer::from_raw_parts(buffer, len)
       }
   }
   ```

